  [9] <a href="javascript:card_browser(240)">Emyn Muil</a><br>
<br>
Free Peoples:<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(299)">Aragorn, Ranger of the North</a><br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(194)">Sting</a> x2<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(11)">Ranger&#39;s Sword</a> x2<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(284)">Glamdring</a> x2<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(283)">Gandalf&#39;s Pipe</a> x2<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(302)">Aragorn&#39;s Pipe</a> x2<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(176)">The Gaffer&#39;s Pipe</a><br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(187)">Old Toby</a> x4<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(183)">Longbottom Leaf</a> x2<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(293)">Servant of the Secret Fire</a> x4<br>
  Sleep Caradhras x2<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(14)">Swordarm of the White Tower</a> x4<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(8)">No Stranger to the Shadows</a> <br>
  Barliman Butterbur<br>
 <br>
Shadow:<br>
  Ulaire Nelya x4<br>
  Ulaire Ostea x2<br>
  Ulaire Cantea x2<br>
  Lurtz x2<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(39)">Troop of Uruk-hai</a> x3<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(43)">Uruk Guard</a> x2<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(856)">Uruk Warrior</a> x3<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(111)">Morgul Blade</a> x3<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(33)">Saruman&#39;s Power</a><br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(112)">Morgul Gates</a> x2<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(104)">Blade Tip</a> x3<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(884)">Saruman&#39;s Snows</a> x2<br>
  <a href="javascript:card_browser(36)">Spies of Saruman</a> x2<br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Papy, Times, serif" class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="  Times, Times New Roman, serif" class="bfont"> Top Cards:<br>
<br><br>
  Your heavy is Aragorn, Ranger of the North, he can exert to play Swordarm of the White Tower giving him a massive strength boost as well as handle a mass of annoying little Goblins.  He&#39;s not alone however, and with buddies like Gandalf, who can play Servant of the Secret Fire, Aragorn can overcome the biggest minions in the game without breaking a sweat!<br>
<br><br>
  The shadow portion relies on getting out those Blade Tips on your opponent and then driving them home with your damage +1 Uruks.  Just one Tip on those wimpy archers can mean death if they meet up with an Uruk-hai.  Cards like Saruman’s Snows and Spies can insure that Hobbits will be left without a place to hide and archers will be spotted before they have a chance to reach into the quiver for another arrow.<br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
How it Beats You<br>
<br><br>
  The early game is set up by going first and stopping at site 2.  This gives you the opportunity to reload your hand to get some minions to play on your opponent.  <br>
<br><br>
  Aragorn is the most expensive card in the deck and you can exert Gandalf to play him for cheap, giving your opponent a hand full of unplayable minions!<br>
<br><br>
  There is method to stopping so early, as minions like Ulaire Nelya will come out to switch your site 2 after your opponent has passed you, giving you a site with +1 move.<br>
<br><br>
  Since your free peoples side is a card drawing machine, use cards like Longbottom Leaf and Old Toby to discard Blade Tips and doubles of your weapons to gain extra cards.  <br>
<br><br>
  The discarded Blade Tips will be used with Morgul Blades and your small, easy to play Nazgul like Ostea, who plays for a mere two twilight with a Morgul Gates, and since he&#39;s a cheap fierce, you get double the chance to Blade Tip that annoying Hobbit or Lord of Gondor - choke decks beware! <br>
<br> <br>
  On your second turn, you can use Nelya to get the +1 move on your Bree Gate and fly by your opponent to arrive at site 4, and possibly 5.<br>
<br><br>
  If he tries to play catchup, your Uruk-hai will rip him to shreds.  The Nazgul are simply softeners for sites 1-4, getting Blade Tips out and allowing Cantea a chance to strip the fellowship of valuble weapons.  The real pain begins after they leave the sanctuary of Rivendell.  Lurtz and company with conditions like Snows and Spies are guaranteed to keep your opponent far behind you, that is, if he&#39;s not burying his dead first!<br>
<br><br>
  With all the pipeweed and pipes, you don&#39;t have to worry about burdens and you can blow off exertion strategies with a couple of puffs from Aragorn&#39;s Pipe.<br>
<br><br>
  Use Sting every chance you get, as it will remove twilight from the pool and give you a chance to see your opponent&#39;s hand to plan your double jumps properly.  Guessing sucks.<br>
<br><br>
  Small Uruks and Saruman&#39;s Power can get those nasty twilight denial and Tale cards off your opponent&#39;s fellowship so you can get big boys like Cantea and the Troop to strip away your opponent&#39;s weapons.<br>
<br><br>
  Use Barliman Butterbur to get back that valuable Servant of the Secret Fire or Sleep, Caradhras to hit your opponent where it counts!  <br>
<br><br>
<br>
<br><br>
#1 Card<br>
<br><br>
  Servant of the Secret Fire, baby!  This card is huge.  It takes the pressure off of Frodo and makes Gandalf and Aragorn instruments of destruction!<br>
<br><br>
